summary: Smut fanfics are realllly weird and gross. Imagine dnp reading that?
question: Smut fanfics are realllly weird and gross. Imagine dnp reading that?
answer: I understand why people like them and it’s perfectly normal to have sexual fantasies, but it is a really bizarre part of modern culture, people posting porn about other real people online where they (and everyone they know) can read it. Dan doesn’t seem to be that concerned with it generally, although I was told that Phil has said that he doesn’t like it and, if that’s true, I do think the right thing for people to do (in an ideal world) is to refrain from posting it. I do think, at the very least, people should be respectful of the fact that Dan and Phil are real people and not appropriate parts of their real lives that have meaning to them and the people they care about for use in porn. I’ve always found the fact that people took Dan’s childhood nickname from his family and turned it into something they use constantly while fetishizing him to be one of the more invasive and disrespectful things the phandom has done. Way to ruin something nice and innocent between him and his loved ones, guys. It’s just the height of entitlement to think that everything in their lives should be ours for the taking.

summary: people in the phandom depend on dan and phil too much. like i get people who may have been 'saved' by their videos, that must...
question: people in the phandom depend on dan and phil too much. like i get people who may have been 'saved' by their videos, that must create an emotional bond, but other people who just watch them  for fun and become obsessed with them and dramatically say they would die if the gaming channel ended and about how they miss them so much, like no offense but dont you have other hobbies or other youtubers to watch? their whole lives revolve dan and phil and it cant be good for their mental health
answer: I agree with this completely. As an audience, we have parasocial relationships with Dan and Phil, not real ones. We interact with content they put out on the internet, but they don’t know us, and we don’t know them outside of their personas. They market themselves as internet friends, but they aren’t our friends. From what I have read, there is evidence to support the fact that parasocial relationships can actually be beneficial for people psychologically, especially those who don’t have a lot of social interaction otherwise. However, I think it is also very easy to get overly-attached and misinterpret the situation, especially for young viewers.

summary: Did you ever read a phanfic?
question: Did you ever read a phanfic?
answer: I have never properly got invested in reading a phanfic, no. My curiosity has gotten the better of me and I have read excerpts of things that have come across my dash, but even then, I have never actually gone to AO3 to finish reading something. I’m not going to lie, there has been a time or two when the writing was good and I was actually tempted, but I don’t really like fan fiction about real people in general because I feel it blurs the lines between who they actually are and a fantasy version of them that a fandom creates through headcanons and tropes. I’m much more interested in the real Dan and what he has to say than a character someone created based on him and have always felt that way.

summary: I’ve been in phandom for 9 years now, and I’ve basically grown up with dnp. As more time passed I prepared myself for dnp...
question: I’ve been in phandom for 9 years now, and I’ve basically grown up with dnp. As more time passed I prepared myself for dnp eventually leaving YouTube, or the public eye altogether. I knew by the time I was an adult they wouldn’t be so prevalent in my life anymore. Now, I am an adult and everything is so uncertain with Dan, the gaming channel, and pretty much all joint content gone. Even Phil seems sick of it all. Do you think this is the end of “Dan And Phil” or do you predict a comeback ahead?
answer: I predict a comeback, but it won’t last long. I feel like maybe we’ll get a couple months where they’re like “Dan’s back! Gaming channel! New merch! Live shows!” And then they’ll fall off the wagon again and be done for good.
